#. <section class="sutta" id="mn62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn62:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 62"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 62"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn62:0.2"
msgid "Mahārāhulovādasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Advice to Rāhula"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.421"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn62:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "mn62:2.2"
msgid ""
"Āyasmāpi kho rāhulo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bhagavantaṃ "
"piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi."
msgstr "And Venerable Rāhula also robed up and followed behind the Buddha."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā apaloketvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha looked back at Rāhula and said:"

msgctxt "mn62:3.2"
msgid ""
"“yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, rūpaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā "
"oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā—sabbaṃ rūpaṃ "
"‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Rāhula, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am "
"not this, this is not my self.’”"

msgctxt "mn62:3.3"
msgid "“Rūpameva nu kho, bhagavā, rūpameva nu kho, sugatā”ti?"
msgstr "“Only form, Blessed One? Only form, Holy One?”"

msgctxt "mn62:3.4"
msgid ""
"“Rūpampi, rāhula, vedanāpi, rāhula, saññāpi, rāhula, saṅkhārāpi, rāhula, "
"viññāṇampi, rāhulā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Form, Rāhula, as well as feeling and perception and choices and "
"consciousness.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. VAR: najja → ko nujja (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn62:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo “ko najja bhagavatā sammukhā ovādena ovadito gāmaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pavisissatī”ti tato paṭinivattitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi "
"pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"Then Rāhula thought: “Who would go to the village for alms today after being "
"advised directly by the Buddha?” Turning back, he sat down at the root of a "
"certain tree cross-legged, with his body straight, and established "
"mindfulness right there."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:5.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle "
"nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr "Venerable Sāriputta saw him sitting there,"

msgctxt "mn62:5.2"
msgid "Disvāna āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed him:"

msgctxt "mn62:5.3"
msgid "“ānāpānassatiṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "“Rāhula, develop mindfulness of breathing."

msgctxt "mn62:5.4"
msgid ""
"Ānāpānassati, rāhula, bhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti "
"mahānisaṃsā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful "
"and beneficial.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.422"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Rāhula came out of retreat, went to the Buddha, "
"bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:7.1"
msgid ""
"“kathaṃ bhāvitā nu kho, bhante, ānāpānassati, kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā "
"hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very "
"fruitful and beneficial?”"

# The text appears to be missing the start of this section.
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Rāhula, the interior earth element is said to be anything hard, solid, and "
"organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:"

#. VAR: nhāru → nahāru (bj, km, pts1) | nhārū (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn62:8.2"
msgid ""
"kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ "
"yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ, yaṃ vā "
"panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, "
"kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, "
"undigested food, feces, or anything else hard, solid, and organic that’s "
"internal, pertaining to an individual."

#. VAR: pathavīdhātu → paṭhavīdhātu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn62:8.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu."
msgstr "This is called the interior earth element."

msgctxt "mn62:8.4"
msgid ""
"Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, "
"pathavīdhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth "
"element."

msgctxt "mn62:8.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn62:8.6"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, "
"pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the earth element, "
"detaching the mind from the earth element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:9.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, āpodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the water element?"

msgctxt "mn62:9.2"
msgid "Āpodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā."
msgstr "The water element may be interior or exterior."

msgctxt "mn62:9.3"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the interior water element?"

msgctxt "mn62:9.4"
msgid "Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Anything that’s water, watery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an "
"individual. This includes:"

msgctxt "mn62:9.5"
msgid ""
"pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā "
"muttaṃ, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial "
"fluid, urine, or anything else that’s water, watery, and organic that’s "
"internal, pertaining to an individual."

msgctxt "mn62:9.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu."
msgstr "This is called the interior water element."

msgctxt "mn62:9.7"
msgid ""
"Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu āpodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water "
"element."

msgctxt "mn62:9.8"
msgid ""
"Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn62:9.9"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the water element, "
"detaching the mind from the water element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:10.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, tejodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the fire element?"

msgctxt "mn62:10.2"
msgid "Tejodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā."
msgstr "The fire element may be interior or exterior."

msgctxt "mn62:10.3"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the interior fire element?"

msgctxt "mn62:10.4"
msgid "Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Anything that’s fire, fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an "
"individual. This includes:"

msgctxt "mn62:10.5"
msgid ""
"yena ca santappati yena ca jīrīyati yena ca pariḍayhati yena ca "
"asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ sammā pariṇāmaṃ gacchati, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci "
"ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"that which warms, that which ages, that which heats you up when feverish, "
"that which properly digests food and drink, or anything else that’s fire, "
"fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual."

msgctxt "mn62:10.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu."
msgstr "This is called the interior fire element."

msgctxt "mn62:10.7"
msgid ""
"Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu tejodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire "
"element."

msgctxt "mn62:10.8"
msgid ""
"Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn62:10.9"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the fire element, "
"detaching the mind from the fire element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.423"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:11.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, vāyodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the air element?"

msgctxt "mn62:11.2"
msgid "Vāyodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā."
msgstr "The air element may be interior or exterior."

msgctxt "mn62:11.3"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the interior air element?"

msgctxt "mn62:11.4"
msgid "Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Anything that’s wind, windy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an "
"individual. This includes:"

#. VAR: koṭṭhāsayā → koṭṭhasayā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn62:11.5"
msgid ""
"uddhaṅgamā vātā, adhogamā vātā, kucchisayā vātā, koṭṭhāsayā vātā, "
"aṅgamaṅgānusārino vātā, assāso passāso iti, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci "
"ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"winds that go up or down, winds in the belly or the bowels, winds that flow "
"through the limbs, in-breaths and out-breaths, or anything else that’s air, "
"airy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual."

msgctxt "mn62:11.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu."
msgstr "This is called the interior air element."

msgctxt "mn62:11.7"
msgid ""
"Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā vāyodhātu yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu vāyodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air "
"element."

msgctxt "mn62:11.8"
msgid ""
"Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn62:11.9"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati, vāyodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the air element, "
"detaching the mind from the air element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:12.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, ākāsadhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the space element?"

msgctxt "mn62:12.2"
msgid "Ākāsadhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā."
msgstr "The space element may be interior or exterior."

msgctxt "mn62:12.3"
msgid "Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu?"
msgstr "And what is the interior space element?"

msgctxt "mn62:12.4"
msgid "Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ ākāsaṃ ākāsagataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Anything that’s space, spacious, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to "
"an individual. This includes:"

#. VAR: maṃsalohitehi upādinnaṃ → ākāsagataṃ upādinnaṃ (bj) | ajjhattaṃ upādiṇṇaṃ (s1) | ajjhattaṃ upādinnaṃ (s2, s3) | ākāsagataṃ upādiṇṇaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: adhobhāgaṃ → adhobhāgā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn62:12.5"
msgid ""
"kaṇṇacchiddaṃ nāsacchiddaṃ mukhadvāraṃ, yena ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ "
"ajjhoharati, yattha ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ santiṭṭhati, yena ca "
"asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ adhobhāgaṃ nikkhamati, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci "
"ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ ākāsaṃ ākāsagataṃ, aghaṃ aghagataṃ, vivaraṃ vivaragataṃ, "
"asamphuṭṭhaṃ, maṃsalohitehi upādinnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"the ear canals, nostrils, and mouth; and the space for swallowing what is "
"eaten and drunk, the space where it stays, and the space for excreting it "
"from the nether regions."

msgctxt "mn62:12.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu."
msgstr "This is called the interior space element."

msgctxt "mn62:12.7"
msgid ""
"Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu yā ca bāhirā ākāsadhātu "
"ākāsadhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior space element and the exterior space element are just the space "
"element."

msgctxt "mn62:12.8"
msgid ""
"Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn62:12.9"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā ākāsadhātuyā cittaṃ nibbindati, "
"ākāsadhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the space element, "
"detaching the mind from the space element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:13.1"
msgid "Pathavīsamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Rāhula, meditate like the earth."

msgctxt "mn62:13.2"
msgid ""
"Pathavīsamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like the earth, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will "
"not occupy your mind."

msgctxt "mn62:13.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, rāhula, pathaviyā sucimpi nikkhipanti, asucimpi nikkhipanti, "
"gūthagatampi nikkhipanti, muttagatampi nikkhipanti, kheḷagatampi "
"nikkhipanti, pubbagatampi nikkhipanti, lohitagatampi nikkhipanti, na ca tena "
"pathavī aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to toss both clean and unclean things on the earth, like "
"feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The earth isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this."

msgctxt "mn62:13.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, pathavīsamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "In the same way, meditate like the earth."

msgctxt "mn62:13.5"
msgid ""
"Pathavīsamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like the earth, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will "
"not occupy your mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.424"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:14.1"
msgid "Āposamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate like water."

msgctxt "mn62:14.2"
msgid ""
"Āposamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ "
"na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like water, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

msgctxt "mn62:14.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, rāhula, āpasmiṃ sucimpi dhovanti, asucimpi dhovanti, "
"gūthagatampi dhovanti, muttagatampi dhovanti, kheḷagatampi dhovanti, "
"pubbagatampi dhovanti, lohitagatampi dhovanti, na ca tena āpo aṭṭīyati vā "
"harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to wash both clean and unclean things in the water, like "
"feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The water isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this."

msgctxt "mn62:14.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, āposamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "In the same way, meditate like water."

msgctxt "mn62:14.5"
msgid ""
"Āposamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ "
"na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like water, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:15.1"
msgid "Tejosamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate like fire."

msgctxt "mn62:15.2"
msgid ""
"Tejosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like fire, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

# BB translates this in line with the previous two, but in fact the syntax is the same as the next: tejo is the subject, the verb is singular, and there is no locative.
msgctxt "mn62:15.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, rāhula, tejo sucimpi dahati, asucimpi dahati, gūthagatampi "
"dahati, muttagatampi dahati, kheḷagatampi dahati, pubbagatampi dahati, "
"lohitagatampi dahati, na ca tena tejo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a fire were to burn both clean and unclean things, like feces, "
"urine, spit, pus, and blood. The fire isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this."

msgctxt "mn62:15.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, tejosamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "In the same way, meditate like fire."

msgctxt "mn62:15.5"
msgid ""
"Tejosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like fire, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:16.1"
msgid "Vāyosamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate like wind."

msgctxt "mn62:16.2"
msgid ""
"Vāyosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like wind, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

msgctxt "mn62:16.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, rāhula, vāyo sucimpi upavāyati, asucimpi upavāyati, gūthagatampi "
"upavāyati, muttagatampi upavāyati, kheḷagatampi upavāyati, pubbagatampi "
"upavāyati, lohitagatampi upavāyati, na ca tena vāyo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā "
"jigucchati vā;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose the wind were to blow on both clean and unclean things, like feces, "
"urine, spit, pus, and blood. The wind isn’t horrified, repelled, and "
"disgusted because of this."

msgctxt "mn62:16.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, vāyosamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "In the same way, meditate like the wind."

msgctxt "mn62:16.5"
msgid ""
"Vāyosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like wind, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:17.1"
msgid "Ākāsasamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate like space."

msgctxt "mn62:17.2"
msgid ""
"Ākāsasamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like space, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

msgctxt "mn62:17.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rāhula, ākāso na katthaci patiṭṭhito;"
msgstr "Just as space is not established anywhere,"

msgctxt "mn62:17.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, ākāsasamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "in the same way, meditate like space."

msgctxt "mn62:17.5"
msgid ""
"Ākāsasamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā "
"cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate like space, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not "
"occupy your mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.425"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:18.1"
msgid "Mettaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on love."

msgctxt "mn62:18.2"
msgid "Mettañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo byāpādo so pahīyissati."
msgstr "For when you meditate on love any ill will will be given up."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:19.1"
msgid "Karuṇaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on compassion."

msgctxt "mn62:19.2"
msgid "Karuṇañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yā vihesā sā pahīyissati."
msgstr "For when you meditate on compassion any cruelty will be given up."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:20.1"
msgid "Muditaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on rejoicing."

msgctxt "mn62:20.2"
msgid "Muditañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yā arati sā pahīyissati."
msgstr "For when you meditate on rejoicing any negativity will be given up."

msgctxt "mn62:20.3"
msgid "Upekkhaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on equanimity."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:21.1"
msgid "Upekkhañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo paṭigho so pahīyissati."
msgstr "For when you meditate on equanimity any repulsion will be given up."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:22.1"
msgid "Asubhaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on ugliness."

msgctxt "mn62:22.2"
msgid "Asubhañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo rāgo so pahīyissati."
msgstr "For when you meditate on ugliness any lust will be given up."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:23.1"
msgid "Aniccasaññaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Meditate on impermanence."

msgctxt "mn62:23.2"
msgid ""
"Aniccasaññañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo asmimāno so pahīyissati."
msgstr ""
"For when you meditate on impermanence any conceit ‘I am’ will be given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:24.1"
msgid "Ānāpānassatiṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi."
msgstr "Develop mindfulness of breathing."

msgctxt "mn62:24.2"
msgid ""
"Ānāpānassati hi te, rāhula, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful "
"and beneficial."

msgctxt "mn62:24.3"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, rāhula, ānāpānassati, kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti "
"mahānisaṃsā?"
msgstr ""
"And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very "
"fruitful and beneficial?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:25.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, rāhula, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to "
"an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and "
"establishes mindfulness right there."

#. VAR: satova → sato (bj, s1, s2, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn62:25.2"
msgid "So satova assasati satova passasati."
msgstr "Just mindful, they breath in. Mindful, they breath out."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:26.1"
msgid ""
"Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When "
"breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’"

msgctxt "mn62:26.2"
msgid ""
"rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When "
"breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’"

msgctxt "mn62:26.3"
msgid ""
"‘Sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing the whole body. They practice "
"breathing out experiencing the whole body."

msgctxt "mn62:26.4"
msgid ""
"‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘passambhayaṃ "
"kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in stilling the body’s motion. They practice "
"breathing out stilling the body’s motion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:27.1"
msgid ""
"‘Pītippaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing rapture. They practice breathing out "
"experiencing rapture."

msgctxt "mn62:27.2"
msgid ""
"‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’"
"ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing bliss. They practice breathing out "
"experiencing bliss."

msgctxt "mn62:27.3"
msgid ""
"‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘"
"cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing these emotions. They practice "
"breathing out experiencing these emotions."

msgctxt "mn62:27.4"
msgid ""
"‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘passambhayaṃ "
"cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in stilling these emotions. They practice breathing "
"out stilling these emotions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:28.1"
msgid ""
"‘Cittappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’"
"ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing the mind. They practice breathing "
"out experiencing the mind."

msgctxt "mn62:28.2"
msgid ""
"‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in gladdening the mind. They practice breathing out "
"gladdening the mind."

msgctxt "mn62:28.3"
msgid ""
"‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in immersing the mind. They practice breathing out "
"immersing the mind."

msgctxt "mn62:28.4"
msgid ""
"‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in freeing the mind. They practice breathing out "
"freeing the mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:29.1"
msgid ""
"‘Aniccānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘aniccānupassī passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in observing impermanence. They practice breathing "
"out observing impermanence."

msgctxt "mn62:29.2"
msgid ""
"‘virāgānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘virāgānupassī passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in observing fading away. They practice breathing "
"out observing fading away."

msgctxt "mn62:29.3"
msgid ""
"‘nirodhānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘nirodhānupassī passasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati;"
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in observing cessation. They practice breathing out "
"observing cessation."

msgctxt "mn62:29.4"
msgid ""
"‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘paṭinissaggānupassī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in observing letting go. They practice breathing out "
"observing letting go."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.426"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:30.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, rāhula, ānāpānassati, evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti "
"mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very "
"fruitful and beneficial."

# PTS’s assasapassasa must be correct, for why else is nirujjhanti plural?
msgctxt "mn62:30.2"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitāya, rāhula, ānāpānassatiyā, evaṃ bahulīkatāya yepi te carimakā "
"assāsā tepi viditāva nirujjhanti no aviditā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way, even "
"when the final breaths in and out cease, they are known, not unknown.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn62:30.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn62:30.4"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Rāhula was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn62:30.5"
msgid "Mahārāhulovādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
